Cosatu says the lack of accountability from Eskom’s board and its management is unacceptable. eNCA's Govan Whittles reports. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Cosatu is calling on Eskom’s board to properly account to Parliament. This after Eskom’s non-executive director Busi Mavuso walked out of a hearing to account to the Standing Committee on Public Accounts. WATCH: Heated exchange between Eskom and SCOPA She’s defended her decision to walk out after telling MPs that the board’s attempts to save Eskom are being hampered by the ANC. But Cosatu says that’s not good enough. * eNCA's Govan Whittles reports.